{"text": "topological superconducting phase based on the invariant in Eq. 106.\n\nA physical consequence of the change of the Pfaffian from a change in flux is the change in\n\nground state fermion parity19,29? associated with such a flux in the set-up shown in Fig. 8. To\n\nunderstand the connection between the Pfaffian and ground state fermion parity, note that\n\nthe two branches of the spectrum that are seen near the zero-energy crossing in Fig. 7(a)\n\nare related by particle-hole symmetry that transforms E \u2192\u2212E and also transforms the\n\ncreation operator \u03c8\u2020 for the state to \u03c8\u2020 \u2192\u03c8. Thus, we can combine these two branches in\n\nterms of the creation operator to\n\nHJJ(\u03c6) \u2248\u03b6(\u03c6 \u2212\u03c0)\u03c8\u2020\n\n\u03c6\u03c8\u03c6.\n\n(128)\n\nNoting that the fermion operator is continuous across \u03c6 \u223c\u03c0 i.e. \u03c8\u2020\n\n\u03c6\u223c\u03c0 \u223c\u03c8\u2020\n\n\u03c6, the crossing\n\nof the pair of Andreev bound states seen in Fig. 7(a) is really a zero crossing of the energy\n\n\u03b6(\u03c6 \u2212\u03c0) of the fermion state with creation operator \u03c8\u2020. Once the energy of such a state\n\ngoes from being negative to positive, we can lower the energy of the system by emptying the\n\n53\n\n\u03a6\n\nSC\n\nnormal lead\n\nV = 0+\n\nVg\n\nnormal lead\n\n(L)\n\n(R)\n\nFIG. 8. (Color online) Andreev level crossing in a topological Josephson junction is associated\n\nwith fermion parity change in topological superconducting ring.\n\nfermion parity change can in\n\nprinciple be detected by Coulomb blockade transport121.\n\nFigure reproduced from Liu et.\n\nal.\n\narXiv:1803.01872121\n\nfermion state. Thus, zero-energy level crossings, which are associated with changes in the\n\nsign of the Pfaffian according to Eq. 42, are also associated with a change in fermion parity.\n\nThis suggests that the sign of the Pfaffian of the BdG Hamiltonian is related to it\u2019s ground\n\nstate fermion parity,